{"type":null,"faqId":26381,"title":"Applicable Scenarios for HDR Mode","answer":"<p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:center;text-indent:21.1pt;\nline-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\">Applicable\nScenarios for HDR Mode</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;text-indent:21.0pt;\nline-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#C00000;\">‚ùÄWhy\nshould we use HDR mode?</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'Times New Roman','serif';color:#006600;\">We see things\nwith our eyes and process what we see with our brains. Speaking from many\naspects, human sight is more advanced than the cameras on high-end smartphones.\nHuman eyes can sense a wide dynamic range, while digital cameras' capabilities\nin this area are limited. That's why when you take photos in scenes with high\ncontrast, the bright areas may look white and the dark areas may look black\n(depending on the exposure you set). </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'Times New Roman','serif'\">Below is a photo taken using P7 in normal mode. </span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#006600;\">In the scene with high contrast, areas with\nlight are white, and those without light are black. </span></p>\n<span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#006600;\n\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20150601203551448001.jpg\" style=\"width:450pt;height:333pt\"></span>\n<br>\n</p>\n<p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'Times New Roman','serif';color:#006600;\">In HDR mode, you\ncan take photos with effects closer to what you see. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'Times New Roman','serif';color:#006600;\">The following\nfigure is taken in HDR mode. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'Times New Roman','serif';color:#006600;\n\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20150601203627706001.jpg\" style=\"width:450pt;height:333pt\"></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'Times New Roman','serif';color:#006600;\n\">\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'Times New Roman','serif';color:#006600;\">It is the same\nscene, but with much better bright and dark details. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'Times New Roman','serif';color:#006600;\">The following are\nmore examples of photos taken in HDR mode.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'Times New Roman','serif';color:#006600;\n\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20150601203653988001.jpg\" style=\"width:450pt;height:333pt\"></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'Times New Roman','serif';color:#006600;\n\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20150601203733828001.jpg\" style=\"width:450pt;height:333pt\"></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;text-indent:21.0pt;\nline-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;text-indent:21.0pt;\nline-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#006600;\">How can we turn on HDR mode?</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;text-indent:21.0pt;\nline-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#006600;\">The P7 is used an example. Open the camera,\ngo to the mode menu, and turn on HDR. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;text-indent:21.0pt;\nline-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#006600;\">However, you are not advised to always use\nHDR mode. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;text-indent:21.1pt;\nline-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Times New Roman','serif';color:#006600;\">When\nshould we use and not use HDR mode?</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;text-indent:21.0pt;\nline-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#006600;\">You are advised to turn on HDR mode only\nwhen necessary, for example, when the scene you are capturing has very bright\nand very dark areas, or if the object you are shooting is covered by shadow. If\nHDR mode is turned on when not required, it may decrease the photo's contrast\nand shadow and make the photo effects unnatural. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;text-indent:21.0pt;\nline-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#006600;\">Avoid shooting moving objects in HDR mode.\nMultiple photos need to be taken to combine into one HDR photo. Therefore,\nevery movement of the shooting object may lead to stitching defects or blurred\nimages. When using HDR mode, keep the shooting object as steady as possible. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;text-indent:21.0pt;\nline-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#006600;\">HDR mode is not applicable to taking\nsnapshots, because your phone needs time to process HDR photos and you will not\nbe able to take another photo in a short period of time. Turn off HDR mode if\nyou want to take multiple photos consecutively. </span></p>\n<br>\n</span></p>\n<br>\n</p>\n<p><br>\n</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"781","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1433162261000,"seriesProductName":"Jazz-L09,Jazz-TL10","visitedTimes":67,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"Applicable Scenarios for HDR Mode","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}